subject: p18615099
Findings: Portable view of the chest is compared to previous exam from. Dual-lead pacing device again seen. Faint bibasilar opacities are seen, particularly in the retrocardiac region which are nonspecific and given low lung volumes could represent atelectasis. There is no definite large pleural effusion. Cardiac silhouette is stable as are the osseous and soft tissue structures.
Impression: No definite acute cardiopulmonary process however, PA and lateral may offer additional detail if desired.
